sentences: Võitmatu armaada '1588. a. Inglismaad vallutama saadetud suur Hispaania laevastik'.
context: In Estonian, 'saadetud' is the past participle form of the verb 'saata,' meaning 'to send.' In this context from a historical text about the Spanish Armada, it describes that a large fleet was sent to conquer England in 1588. The word specifically indicates something that has been dispatched or sent for a particular purpose.
